<subSubSection id="99C96513FFACFF80FF36F59B84B9F1C2" box="[199,950,691,717]" pageId="16" pageNumber="397" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="D16C3698FFACFF80FF36F59B84B9F1C2" blockId="16.[151,1437,402,789]" box="[199,950,691,717]" pageId="16" pageNumber="397">
<emphasis id="E3A7EA8AFFACFF80FF36F59B8641F1C2" bold="true" box="[199,334,691,717]" pageId="16" pageNumber="397">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named for its short (
<taxonomicName id="16D34D1BFFACFF80FD13F59B842AF1C2" box="[738,805,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hecaloidella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="397" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevis">
<emphasis id="E3A7EA8AFFACFF80FD13F59B842AF1C2" box="[738,805,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="397">brevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) connective.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="99C96513FFACFF80FF36F5FF8671F01A" pageId="16" pageNumber="397" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D16C3698FFACFF80FF36F5FF8671F01A" blockId="16.[151,1437,402,789]" pageId="16" pageNumber="397">
<emphasis id="E3A7EA8AFFACFF80FF36F5FF8634F1FE" bold="true" box="[199,315,727,753]" pageId="16" pageNumber="397">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished from all other 
<taxonomicName id="16D34D1BFFACFF80FCABF5FF84E4F1FE" authorityName="Osborn" authorityYear="1934" box="[858,1003,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hecaloidella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="397" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E3A7EA8AFFACFF80FCABF5FF84E4F1FE" box="[858,1003,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="397">Hecaloidella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by the unique shape of its connective (
<figureCitation id="49E82A1DFFACFF80FF06F5D3867DF01A" box="[247,370,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1845,1869]" captionTargetBox="[222,1372,183,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-17@17.[211,1377,181,1821]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 7. Male genitalia and female pregenital sternite of H. quadripicta species group; Aâ€“G, H. brevis; A, aedeagus, lateral view; B, apex of aedeagus, lateral view; C, aedeagus, ventral view; Dâ€“E, connective, dorsal and lateral view; F, valve and subgenital plate, dorsal view; G, style; Hâ€“L, H. brunnifacialis; H, aedeagus and connective, lateral view; I, aedeagus, caudal view; J, style; K, connective, ventral view; L, female pregenital sternite; Mâ€“Q, H. knighti; M, aedeagus, ventral view; N, connective, ventral view; O, style; P, aedeagus and connective, lateral view; Q, female pregenital sternite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4629116" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4629116/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="397">Fig. 7Dâ€“E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
